Name: The Point at Old Man's
Description: A lovely, lazy, break to split with groms and seniors; fire pits and palapas on the beach, nuclear power on the cliffs.

Name: Little Corona
Description: Gem cove with tidepools and occasional body thumpers; gateway to Arch Rock.

Name: UCSB
Description: Once an Marine Corps Air Station until 1949, now the University I call home.

Name: Devereaux/Coal Oil Point
Description: Where a marine petroleom oil seepage meets a right point break rivaling Rincon.

Name: Andrew Molera
Description: Taking off at the point, the break traces the line between fresh water river and open ocean, with a panoramic view of Big Sur.

Name: Matthole Beach
Description: At the north end of King Range - northen Lost Coast boundary - where the Matthole introduces endangered Steelhead, Coho & Chinnook Salmon to a wild sea.

Name: Coos Bay
Description: Definition of "fishing town" insulated by dense forest; routes between surf breaks double as canoe fishing routes.
